<br>
A year ago, I left and people were talking about ALWAYS keeping Trak on Reservations.  I come back and the first thing I read &quot;Vote on Trak...&quot;.<br>
<br>
Would you rather be more free with the oppourtinity for more loot and good times, or have your freedom restricted so everyone gets their fair share?<br>
<br>
You can make everyone have equal oppourtunity, but in a system where the resources are finite and the population grows, everyone will grow equally miserable.<br>
<br>
Edit:<br>
One last thing... if you apply this raiding scheme to a macroeconomic model the people who are left out of raids because all of the positions are taken are the Unemployed.  Now every freedom loving Economic system has a natural rate of unemployment 2-3%, and most of the unemployed aren't unemployed for long.  The people who are constantly unemployed (non-cyclical unemployment), aren't worthy of being employed (raiding) at all.  They don't have the drive to go out and do things to better themselves, so they are always dragging down the bottom of the curve.<br>
<br>
If everything suddenly went FCFS, there would be a mad rush for resources (like you saw when the USSR collapsed) and everything would seem scarce and chaotic.  Given time, everything will balance out.  Guilds will have gotten everything they can from a certain MoB and move on.  Guilds will get sick of clearing Hate and take time off.  Specific Guilds raiding certain areas will be constant for a while (initially) but will eventually become cyclical (think sine wave) giving rise to other guilds taking its place (think cosine).  There will be constant raiding, but eventually if logic means anything at all everyone will have a fair shot if they put forth enough effort.  Will your plans get stepped on every now and then?  Yes.  So will everyone elses. <p>_________________<br>
